This paper proposes a methodology for learning graph node embeddings in an unsupervised way, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The paper focuses on the structural properties of the graph and how they affect the performance of existing methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the use of personalized PageRank, which is a common algorithm in information retrieval (cs.IR) and graph theory (cs.DS).
